Canada's Inflation Cools Down in June Canada's annual inflation rate dipped to 2.7% in June, according to Statistics Canada. This welcome slowdown is primarily attributed to a decrease in the year-over-year growth of gasoline prices. Following a significant 5.6% jump in May, gasoline prices rose by a more modest 0.4% in June. Excluding gasoline, the Consumer Price Index (CPI) still showed some inflation, with a year-over-year increase of 2.8%. To learn more find the CTV News article linked below.

Seattle Makes History with Jessica Campbell, NHL's First Full-Time Woman Coach. Continuing her successful partnership with coach Dan Bylsma, Jessica Campbell becomes the NHL's first full-time female coach, joining the Seattle Kraken staff.
